(171342, '68B91400-B376-45DC-8AFD-08F6DBFEE8F5', ' I felt a little weird after our call this afternoon. I know you were just trying to communicate that it is an adjustment for you to prioritize boyfriend time, which i very much appreciate, but it made me feel like doing so was in some way making a sacrifice. I know that being very socially active feeds you, and is important for your work/career...I get this and I love this about you. I''m designed a bit differently in this respect and coming from a different experience and have my own set of (major) adjustments...single divorced dad....with some new free time.  Im used to pretty much all non-work time being parenting/family time. It has been hard for me to find the time to maintain friendships much less build new ones...and especially the last 2 years where i really withdrew to just deal with what is in front of me. Plus, I need alone time to rejuvenate, make music, read. I love the vision of us being able to have our own lives...have separate experiences  and shared experiences.   I''ll share one memory, and a thought. I remember being at a party with Marla when the boys were just toddlers...it was an adult event at someone''s house...and they were just running around and I had to keep my eyes on them pretty much the whole time...marla would get engaged in a conversation and forget they were there when I''d ask to keep an eye out. After the party she was like ''did you meet any interesting people and have good discussions?'' I was like, ''no...I was too busy making sure the kids didn''t fall down the stairs.''  Also, when I started considering the prospect of dating, my initial thought was I''d probably end up with someone who already has kids...that the shared experience of feeling that you don''t really matter as much anymore and needing to put your needs/wants last for extended periods of time would be important to have in common. I don''t think this is necessarily True I guess these things trigger a fear for me....it is my shit, I know. I feel our time together is precious and I know it can be challenging to fit it all in.  Getting sleepy and probably not that coherent anymore. More to discuss together...', '464248621000000000', '464249486000000000', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'David', '2015-09-17T22:57:01'),
